          },
          "datePublished": "2023-01-11",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Manav Bharti India International School was established in 1941 by Dr Durga Prasad Pandey. It's a co-educational English medium school in affiliation with the CBSE board offering education to the students from I to XII. The school creates an environment for learning which is innovative, enjoyable and which encourages intellectual curiosity. The school has spacious and well-maintained classrooms, well-equipped laboratories, a computer lab, a well-stocked library, an auditorium, dance & music room, an art club etc. They also teach languages like Hindi, Sanskrit, German and French along with English. The school campus is located in a noise-free and pollution-free environment, creating a peaceful atmosphere to learn. The school has a large sports field providing facilities for basketball, volleyball, hockey, badminton, kho-kho, football, table tennis and cricket. The well-trained and friendly faculty, help in the overall development of their students. The objective of this school is to create self-reliant and broad-minded citizens who selflessly participate in the nation's progress. They emphasize the social, moral, spiritual, physical and mental development of each child.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
